{"word":"νεάω","slug":"νεάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νεάω</b></el> <el>(νεάω,) ( φυτ. <el>-άσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νέος'><el>νέος</el></a>\n<p/><i>to plough up anew</i>, of fallow land, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>agros novare</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>νεωμένη</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>γῆ</el>) <i>land new-ploughed</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>novale</el>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/>"}]}